page.title: 08WOODLAND AREAS
page.content: IN THE NORTH OF THE BLOCK THE MAJOR LAND COVER IS WOODLAND, ESPECIALLY BEECH, OAK AND CONIFERS. THERE IS PLENTY OF EVIDENCE THAT THE WOODLAND IS COMMERCIALLY MANAGED; PILES OF FELLED TREES AND LOGS, FRESH PLANTATIONS AND MACHINERY ARE EASY TO FIND. THE TREES ARE QUITE WELL SPACED AND A VARIETY OF FERNS AND WILD FLOWERS PROVIDE GROUND COVER. SEVERAL TRACKS AND FOOTPATHS PROVIDE ACCESS TO THE CLEARINGS AND ENCLOSURES. IN ONE OF THESE, WOOLMERS, IS A DOG KENNELS. THE LANDSCAPE IN THE WOODED AREAS IS FAIRLY HILLY, BETWEEN 50 AND 170 METRES ABOVE SEA LEVEL.
